https://leetcode.com/problems/subtree-of-another-tree/description/

QUESTION:
Input: root = [3,4,5,1,2], subRoot = [4,1,2]
Output: true

SOLUTION:
The optimal approach is serialization which is given after solving two naive approaches.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
OPTIMAL APPROACH: Is serialization
TIME COMPLEXITY: O(n+m)
SPACE COMPLEXITY: O(n+m)

Approach:
Serialize then
root -> (3,(4,(1,N,N),(2,N,N)),(5,N,N))
Sub Root Value -> (4,(1,N,N),(2,N,N))

/**
 * Definition for a binary tree node.
 * public class TreeNode {
 *     int val;
 *     TreeNode left;
 *     TreeNode right;
 *     TreeNode() {}
 *     TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
 *     TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
 *         this.val = val;
 *         this.left = left;
 *         this.right = right;
 *     }
 * }
 */
class Solution {
    public String serialize(TreeNode root){
        if(root==null)return "N";
    }
    public boolean isSubtree(TreeNode root, TreeNode subRoot) {
        String rootValue=serialize(root);
        String subRootValue=serialize(subRoot);
        return rootValue.contains(subRootValue);
    }
}
